modules.description: This module removes diacritics from Latin letters in UTF8 strings, converting characters like "é" to "e", and handles malformed or non-ASCII input with customizable replacements. It operates on standard strings and individual Unicode characters (Uchar.t), offering functions to simplify text for searching and comparison while preserving ASCII output when configured. Specific use cases include normalizing user input for case-insensitive matching and stripping accents from text imported from legacy encodings like ISO-8859-1 or Windows-1252.
